{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.37",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 37,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 37",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 37 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:1",
      "text": "“At this also my heart trembles, and leaps out of its place.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:2",
      "text": "Hearken to the thunder of his voice and the rumbling that comes from his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:3",
      "text": "Under the whole heaven he lets it go, and his lightning to the corners of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:4",
      "text": "After it his voice roars; he thunders with his majestic voice and he does not restrain the lightnings when his voice is heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:5",
      "text": "God thunders wondrously with his voice; he does great things which we cannot comprehend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:6",
      "text": "For to the snow he says, ‘Fall on the earth’; and to the shower and the rain, ‘Be strong.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:7",
      "text": "He seals up the hand of every man, that all men may know his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:8",
      "text": "Then the beasts go into their lairs, and remain in their dens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:9",
      "text": "From its chamber comes the whirlwind, and cold from the scattering winds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:10",
      "text": "By the breath of God ice is given, and the broad waters are frozen fast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:11",
      "text": "He loads the thick cloud with moisture; the clouds scatter his lightning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:12",
      "text": "They turn round and round by his guidance, to accomplish all that he commands them on the face of the habitable world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:13",
      "text": "Whether for correction, or for his land, or for love, he causes it to happen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:14",
      "text": "“Hear this, O Job; stop and consider the wondrous works of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:15",
      "text": "Do you know how God lays his command upon them, and causes the lightning of his cloud to shine?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:16",
      "text": "Do you know the balancings of the clouds, the wondrous works of him who is perfect in knowledge,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:17",
      "text": "you whose garments are hot when the earth is still because of the south wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:18",
      "text": "Can you, like him, spread out the skies, hard as a molten mirror?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:19",
      "text": "Teach us what we shall say to him; we cannot draw up our case because of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:20",
      "text": "Shall it be told him that I would speak? Did a man ever wish that he would be swallowed up?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:21",
      "text": "“And now men cannot look on the light when it is bright in the skies, when the wind has passed and cleared them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:22",
      "text": "Out of the north comes golden splendor; God is clothed with terrible majesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:23",
      "text": "The Almighty—we cannot find him; he is great in power and justice, and abundant righteousness he will not violate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.37.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:24",
      "text": "Therefore men fear him; he does not regard any who are wise in their own conceit.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
